  "background": "white",
  "title": {
    "text": "Smoking prevalence has declined over time",
    "subtitle": [
      "The decline after 2016 may be associated with overlapping policy,",
      "market, and behavioural changes around 2015–2016.",
      "In 2015, excise duties increased sharply, and GST added further",
      "price pressure, making legal cigarettes less affordable for many smokers.",
      "By 2016, analysts expected tobacco volume to decline because",
      "prices had moved beyond the pain threshold.",
      "At the same time, Malaysia strengthened tobacco control, while vaping,",
      "cessation support, and illicit cigarettes changed how some smokers responded.",
      "Overall, the later decline should be read as overlapping",
      "pressures, rather than one single factor."
    ],
